				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: soloing casters<a name="72417"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 25 05 2:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It will try and malo you, slow you, nuke you, dot you and root you.
<br />

<br />
Of these, root is the only problem as you can cure/dispel DoTs and the nukes are feeble.
<br />

<br />
1) Just keep MR resists up, you will resist pretty well any roots. Use the MR Psalm I guess as you dont have the luxury of the Chorus songs yet. Dunno if you have your epic.
<br />

<br />
2) Keep dispell memmed and the top two, or preferably three buff slots free.  IF somehow it lands a root/dot you can dispel.
<br />

<br />
3) Keep Aria of Ascetism disease/poison cure memmed for disease dots, if he slows you it dont matter (assuming you are kiting). You do have this song I trust =)
<br />

<br />
As for mez and dot, yes that would be quite bonkers.  What they are saying I bet is to mez and drain. But at lvl 52 you dont have a worthwhile mana drain.  One thing you CAN do with mez is, if he is woppin your a$. Mezz him and regen yourself with a lute.
<br />

<br />
Shaman NPC's are wussy.
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
